 to get properly immersed in what i'm playing!).\n\nThe lack of direct control too is something i feel is a pretty good direction, you give overall 'comamnds' and let the wee rats go about their business fulfilling them. Not only does this make for some very interesting gameplay, but also gives a sense of how i'd imagine a rat colony to function (lots of scurrying). \n\nThe ability to customize your soldiers in armour and arms is awesome, as is the use of both range and melee weapons. Its small touches of detail like this that make this title shine. The economy aspect is also pretty nice, being complex but easy to get to grips with (a lot of resources, but a simpligied hands-off means of collection). \n\nI've by no means got to grips with this game yet (Indeed i get getting absolutely trounced by the AI- another positive being its difficulty and ability to fight effectively against a player) and look forward to getting back to trying to get my first victory.\n\nThings i would like to see improved upon would be the ability to perhaps have more than two kingdoms fight it out on a map, as well as more content (maybe a campaign or a few different game modes?). Basically just MOAR! :).\n\nWould thourghly recommend. And as of 1/2/17 its still being updated, achievements and trading cards- so my favourite past time of achievement hunting is a go- still getting my arse kicked though.. so that's the 'defeat' one easy enough :P", "received_for_free": false, "author": {"playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "steamid": "76561198018449587", "last_played": 1485971835, "num_reviews": 14, "num_games_owned": 623, "playtime_forever": 186}, "votes_up": 8, "timestamp_created": 1474973998, "written_during_early_access": false, "weighted_vote_score": "0.511115", "votes_down": 5, "timestamp_updated": 1485971961, "recommendationid": "25722936", "votes_funny": 1, "voted_up": true}, {"language": "english", "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "review": "Very interesting little game. The aesthe